               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18150621-66-person596">
                  JAMES 
                  GODSELL
               <interp inst="t18150621-66-person596" type="surname" value="GODSELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150621-66-person596" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150621-66-person596" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an apprentice to the Crown printing office. I bought the duplicate from the three prisoners at the bar, for sixpence. The prisoners were all three together. Mr. Vaughan got the duplicate from me.</p>
               <p>Thackery's Defence. That officer has a spite against me, and he swore if he could not do any thing else with me, he would police me.</p>
               <p>THACKERY, <rs id="t18150621-66-verdict381" type="verdictDescription">
